&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gersh is a leading global entertainment and sports agency, representing a diverse roster of clients across film, television, sports, theater, comedy, branding, publishing, and digital media. As the fastest-growing major agency, Gersh is respected for its hands-on, client-first approach and commitment to driving innovation and success. Following an equity investment from Crestview Partners in 2023 Gersh has advanced its long-term growth plan, acquiring the Digital and Alternative departments of the A3 Agency, and You First – one of the world’s top sports and entertainment agencies. With clients at the heart of every growth decision, Gersh is harnessing strategic insights and decades of experience to strengthen its resources, empowering clients to realize success across all areas of the media landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gersh is looking to hire a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Associate (Coordinator)&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;to support the Personal Appearances, Signings, and Conventions Department. This role plays a key role in supporting the booking, strategy, and execution of talent appearances, fan convention appearances, autograph signings, promotional events, and brand partnerships. This position works closely with agents, managers, clients, promoters, brokers, and buyers to help identify opportunities, manage relationships, and ensure successful deal execution. [*Note: &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Candidates will be considered for either the NYC or Beverly Hills, CA office locations&lt;/span&gt;.]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is proactive, collaborative, highly organized, and passionate about entertainment, talent representation, and live events. This role is best suited for someone interested in developing a career in conventions, autograph and trading card signings, and personal appearances.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Gersh Conventions department connects their clients (actors, athletes, and other recognizable talent) with the producers and promoters of fan-based conventions (“Comic Cons”), events, private autograph signings, and other similar appearances. This department facilitates all aspects of talent representation and coordination including pitching for and procuring paid opportunities, negotiating deals, facilitating payments, creating detailed itineraries, and covering clients on a global scale.&amp;nbsp;This position will report to the Department Head (Vice President, Personal Appearances, Signings, and Conventions).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Personal Appearances, Signings &amp;amp; Conventions department in securing and managing talent bookings for appearances, conventions, signings, and promotional events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate directly with promoters, event organizers, buyers, brokers, and clients regarding booking opportunities and event logistics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong professional relationships with industry partners and talent representatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in evaluating incoming offers, preparing deal terms, and tracking booking activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and oversee talent travel, event schedules, and appearance-related deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare booking materials, appearance schedules, and client presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor industry trends, convention calendars, and emerging appearance opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal departments on marketing, branding, publicity, and client initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help manage event attendance and provide on-site support when required.&lt;/li&gt;
